data.jamchart_notes: A propulsive Trevor-led groove gives way to some gentle arpeggiator accentuation from Peter under a mellow Summery vibe. data.jamchart_notes: Typical 2024 "Saints" jamming hits a solid peak before downshifting into several minutes of cool groovy funk. Peter in particular covers some subtle sonic ground on organ here. The band pivots into bliss and builds beautifully into THE DROP just after 24 minutes. Excellent version that breaks the monotony "Myst" jams had been getting into.

data.shownotes: This show marked the debut of a new stage setup: (from left to right) Peter, Rick, Trevor, Cotter, and Jeff on a riser behind.

data.jamchart_notes: Eschews the standard 2024 "Saints" motif in favour of a slow and breathtakingly gorgeous jam. Peter leans hard into the Vintage Vibe as Rick pours an incredible amount of emotion into his solo.

data.jamchart_notes: First show-opening version ever sets the tone for an incredible night with an efficient and well-paced peak jam.

Beautiful, patient segue -> from "Ride Like The Wind." Jam spends some time in the typical major-key "Myst" mode before Peter goes wild on delayed piano. Some cacophony enters as Rick sticks to driving rhythm work. Fantastic peak that gradually winds down over the final few minutes and > to "Give it Time."

data.jamchart_notes: Rick takes the reins and makes another strong entry into the book of Cotter-era bliss "Myst" jams. He finds a melodic hook to build the peak around and just does that, eventually winding down into a calm outro that resolves into "Hungersite."

data.jamchart_notes: Absolutely incredible upbeat disco build. Rick leads the way and Cotter is right alongside him with some patient builds as they avoid an easy path into the Goontz. Cools after 21 mins as Peter takes out his sequenced percussion loops and Rick and Trevor circle each other's melodies in the open space (with a nice Sublime tease thrown in). Beautifully winds its way -> into an all-timer "Fish in the Sea" from there.

data.jamchart_notes: Rick wastes no time in establishing a jam that is heavily reminiscent of Wanna Be Starting Something for a couple minutes of MJ dance party. The band reboots with a brief interlude of psychedelic searching. Cotter cuts through with the hi-hat as Rick plucks through a propulsive groove that becomes the centerpiece of the next 9 minutes, unleashing a high energy jam featuring the crunchy octave down guitar work and GOONTZ-y drops that have become the hallmark of 2025.
data.venuename: Mann Center for the Performing Arts

data.shownotes: The show began where the previous show left off - Rick walked up on stage and turned on the light as a choir began to sing a drone off stage. The choir then joined after the first chorus. During Marb House, a UV Dance Party commenced with characters dancing on stage and painting all the set props with UV paint. During the encore all of the characters and puppets appeared as well as two aerialists. There was also a balloon drop and confetti during Dramophone. The show ended with the veil opening back up, after the veil sequence, the characters, puppets, choir, and band had vanished. This show was part of Goosemas XII.
